thread.title: Oil Prices Mixed as Supply Uncertainty Continues

author: Amrith Ramkumar
title: Oil Prices Mixed as Supply Uncertainty Continues
text:
Oil prices were mixed Thursday after data showed a larger-than-expected decrease in U.S. stockpiles last week, but investors continued debating the future of the production-cut deal that has boosted prices.
U.S. crude futures fell 1.2% to $67.38 a barrel on the New York Mercantile Exchange after ending a five-session losing streak a day earlier. Brent crude, the global benchmark, added 0.3%, to $77.73 a barrel.
